"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"i have recently been playing [defi kingdoms](https://game.defikingdoms.com) on the harmony blockchain; an on-chain medieval-themed game in your browser that features a gamified decentralized exchange (dex) for swapping token pairs.\\n\\ndexs aren’t particularly novel (see uniswap, pancakeswap etc) — what’s novel, in this case, is the use of engaging lore (storytelling) to present existing financial concepts/tools that fit perfectly into an overarching theme/story.\\n\\n![druid lazarus serves as an interface to the liquidity pool](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/ZXJuNHYRg_ukJoEO7kf96.png?height=2100&width=3360)\\n\\nliquidity pools are “gardens” in the defi kingdom universe; when liquidity is provided to a pool with a token pair, we get “seeds” representing your position in the pool i.e lp tokens.\\n\\non one hand, this could be a really elaborate ponzi wrapped with great storytelling; on another, it’s a perfect example of how mundane financial/defi primitives (liquidity pools, dexs, amms) could be made engaging, accessible, and interesting through literature and storytelling.\\n\\ni’m super interested in seeing more examples of great lore + financial primitives built into the mechanics of (experimental) games in the future.\",\"timestamp\":1641304571,\"title\":\"liquidity pools, lore and crypto\"},\"digest\":\"rsIMG6mX2U3na_D2ove9_cnXaSvJSUMFFrjNWnh1Jcs\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0xa7379735e29eC9743A40A023d7ace40b294B4F17\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"alg\\\":\\\"ES256\\\",\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"Bw0aVM5tRlFvRyaqz4jSN_Q1V0wiies_z7DQr7MYO3U\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"Qw5qtgSOtCAETEWpWS5tGjUXkRiHnGyBbNcgp0t1XDg\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"OgGeO5nmMzXIvdMyKPJg9ltqR8GcSNNkxxvL6h3jv9jpHjsKDR848wXF-mrfrQJGJkID53J8Bx27-xaJxCnzWA\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0xdee5ff23169a2b742c15db1c8254810455b90dc70fcbd90dfeda21e299f32ef04733d72d4e34bbede0c3912c257465b